{"TopicId":215827,"ForumId":197,"TopicTitle":"Sun glare appears through mountains","CreatedByName":"Reesey","CreatedById":228195,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T09:56:18Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Reesey","CreatedById":228195,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T09:56:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP: v0.1.1.0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWin 11\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCPU 3900X\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGPU RTX 3080\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nto replicate, go to the source opf the huge river opposite \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E on Kerbin. Wait for the sunrise.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022?imw=2048\u0026amp;imh=1152\u0026amp;ima=fit\u0026amp;impolicy=Lett\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002296.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/2037355910744039137/A65B2A1DFD869402A5A279731A45600ED71B90B7/?imw=2048\u0026amp;imh=1152\u0026amp;ima=fit\u0026amp;impolicy=Letterbox\u0026amp;imcolor=%23000000\u0026amp;letterbox=true\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tazooka","CreatedById":226666,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T12:52:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOther celestial bodies too\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022226666\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed2365789013\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/215537-solar-flare-visible-through-minmus-ground/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:149px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"darthgently","CreatedById":204885,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T13:03:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224264851\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215827\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679662356\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022226666\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Tazooka\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, Tazooka said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOther celestial bodies too\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022226666\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed7395916667\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/215537-solar-flare-visible-through-minmus-ground/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:172px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf Minmus is translucent glass it could almost make sense under the right conditions when the flare is just below the horizon I suppose, and nice, but clearly a glitch if on all bodies\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOf course if it were too be used intentionally for Minmus it would need to look a lot different than as captured above\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tazooka","CreatedById":226666,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T13:47:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224264854\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215827\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679663012\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022204885\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022darthgently\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n42 minutes ago, darthgently said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf Minmus is translucent glass it could almost make sense under the right conditions when the flare is just below the horizon I suppose, and nice, but clearly a glitch if on all bodies\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOf course if it were too be used intentionally for Minmus it would need to look a lot different than as captured above\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0Definitely a bug and not intentional. The Mun has the same issue\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"darthgently","CreatedById":204885,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T15:41:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224264868\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215827\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679665647\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022226666\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Tazooka\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Tazooka said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0Definitely a bug and not intentional. The Mun has the same issue\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat is what I wrote.\u00A0 Was just pointing out it would be a cool effect for a translucent glass moon.\u00A0 But thanks for skimming nearly half of what I wrote, your efforts are appreciated! \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}